EPISODE 8

5
00:00:49,220 --> 00:00:50,300
By the way,

6
00:00:52,220 --> 00:00:54,510
I actually don't have…

7
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:08,570
…amnesia.

8
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,210
I don't have amnesia.

9
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,590
I was acting all along.

10
00:01:28,380 --> 00:01:29,470
Hard to believe?

11
00:01:30,050 --> 00:01:31,050
I don't blame you.

12
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,680
I was also surprised by
how good of an actor I was.

13
00:01:35,390 --> 00:01:38,480
Okay, then. Shall we talk
about our first meeting?

14
00:01:39,180 --> 00:01:41,690
You showed up on February 21 of last year

15
00:01:41,770 --> 00:01:44,230
at 9:53 and 28 seconds.

16
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:47,940
You wore tacky gray plaid pants
and black loafers

17
00:01:48,030 --> 00:01:49,860
and interrupted my reading time.

18
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:52,200
Since that very day,
you totally got on my nerves!

19
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:56,990
You didn't follow the 5.5cm binder rule,

20
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,910
your meeting minutes were
wordy like a novel,

21
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,500
and you got me drinking tea
when I asked for a driver.

22
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:04,960
Worst of all, your lukewarm coffee was
so bad that even a dog wouldn't drink it!

23
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,000
But…

24
00:02:07,090 --> 00:02:08,840
the real highlight…

25
00:02:10,590 --> 00:02:11,760
was at my vacation house.

26
00:02:17,260 --> 00:02:18,100
Hey!

27
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:20,930
Hey! Do you think I let that slide
because I was scared of you?

28
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,480
No, I didn't want to waste my time.

29
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,690
-Because you're a worthless loser.
-Because you're a worthless loser.

30
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,900
-No, actually, I never got back at you
-No, actually, I never got back at you

31
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,150
-because you were not even worth my time!
-because you were not even worth my time!

32
00:02:30,530 --> 00:02:31,360
What do you think?

33
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:36,530
I have it perfectly memorized
word for word, don't I?

34
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,070
But

35
00:03:17,450 --> 00:03:19,330
fainting was a little lame.

36
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,120
"It's me. Your fiancée."

37
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:29,040
That was totally awesome, don't you think?

38
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:32,510
I wasn't the only one
who was good at acting.

39
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,930
My fiancée was very good too.
You gave me goosebumps.

40
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:40,180
You were terrible at your job,

41
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:43,430
but it turns out
that you had great acting skills.

42
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,480
Why don't you try switching careers
while you're at it?

43
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:49,310
I'm so sorry.

44
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:53,150
Thanks to you, I got to eat so many onions

45
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:55,280
and even got covered in vomit.

46
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,660
It even got inside my ear.

47
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:03,200
I suffered so much
because of you, my fiancée.

48
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,830
How do you plan to make up for all this?

49
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:09,170
I'm so sorry, Mr. Noh.

50
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:10,540
No need to say sorry.

51
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:12,960
You can just serve your time in prison.

52
00:04:15,340 --> 00:04:20,300
You punched holes everywhere
on my limited edition suits and vase.

53
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:23,520
You turned my cacti into cucumbers,

54
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,640
charged everything
on my corporate credit card,

55
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:26,810
and even scratched my car.

56
00:04:28,230 --> 00:04:30,610
That's easily over a billion won.

57
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,230
On top of it,
you pretended to be my fiancée.

58
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:36,150
Isn't that…

59
00:04:37,030 --> 00:04:38,950
considered fraud?

60
00:04:41,780 --> 00:04:43,370
With all that, you'd make the news.

61
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,660
"Pretending to be his fiancée,

62
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,330
commits a billion-won fraud."

63
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:52,210
You'd better find a lawyer soon.

64
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:57,300
And make sure you tell this
to Mr. Lee Yonggu in Gangwon Province.

65
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,800
His tiny house and land

66
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:04,390
will all be seized.

67
00:05:04,970 --> 00:05:06,560
A father should pay

68
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:09,270
for his daughter's fraud.

69
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:13,150
Sudden shock could be
detrimental to the elderly.

70
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:16,690
Make sure you tell him ahead,
so that he doesn't pass away.

71
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:19,280
Right.

72
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,370
What the heck are you doing?

73
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:24,950
No!

74
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:29,620
Dad!

75
00:05:29,710 --> 00:05:31,790
Dad! Get up, Dad!

76
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,630
What do you think you're doing?

77
00:05:33,710 --> 00:05:35,840
Dad!

78
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:38,130
-You're under arrest for fraud.
-What?

79
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:41,180
Dad!

80
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:45,890
Lee Sina, the accused, took advantage
of victim Noh Gojin having amnesia

81
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:47,640
and pretended to be his fiancée

82
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,560
causing him one billion won
worth of damages.

83
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:51,730
And as she shows no sign of remorse,

84
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:54,270
I, therefore, sentence her
to ten years in prison.

85
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,980
No!

86
00:05:58,070 --> 00:06:00,860
No, you can't do this!

87
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:06,370
Sir, I'm sorry!
I think I really lost my mind.

88
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:08,910
I beg for your forgiveness
just this once. Please.

89
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,210
You all say the same, boring things.

90
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:16,210
You know I'm not a pushover
who forgives people.

91
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:21,760
There is, isn't there?

92
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:24,930
Sorry?

93
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:27,970
Who is it?

94
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,520
Who ordered you to do it?

95
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:34,100
What do you mean, who ordered me?

96
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:37,940
There's no such thing.
No one ordered me to do it.

97
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:40,690
No one ordered you to do it,

98
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:45,450
yet you happened to lure me
out of my vacation house at that moment,

99
00:06:45,620 --> 00:06:49,870
I happened to get hit by a car
while I was talking to you on the phone,

100
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:51,830
and again,

101
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:55,710
you happened to take me to the hospital

102
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,460
suddenly as my fiancée?

103
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,920
That's because…

104
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:10,810
But seriously, no one ordered me to do it.
It was me. I did it all on my own.

105
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,270
Is that so?

106
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:18,730
So you did it on your own too?

107
00:07:22,530 --> 00:07:23,450
Fine.

108
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,530
My hands are tied.

109
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:28,910
You need to disappear too then.

110
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:30,790
To prison.

111
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:35,870
No, sir! Wait! Please!

112
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:38,960
I'll pay it back.
I'll pay it back however I can,

113
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,760
so please spare my father's house.
I beg you.

114
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,380
I'll do anything you ask for.

115
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:45,260
Sir, please. Just this once.

116
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,550
You'll do anything?

117
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,010
Yes.

118
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:54,430
-Seriously?
-Yes, anything. I'll do anything.

119
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:57,560
I beg for your forgiveness
just this once. Please.

120
00:07:57,650 --> 00:07:58,900
Please, sir.

121
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:00,650
Please.

122
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:33,810
PAYMENT AGREEMENT CONTRACT

123
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,350
Sign it.

124
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,350
What's… this?

125
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,770
A hostage contract.

126
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,190
Hostage?

127
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:47,990
OUTSTANDING LIABILITIES

128
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:51,910
"As of today,
Lee Sina is Noh Gojin's hostage."

129
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:53,660
Something like that.

130
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:55,250
TO OFFSET LIABILITIES WITH LABOR

131
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:58,330
CONTINUE TO ACT AS FIANCÉE,
WORK AS DRIVER AND HOUSEKEEPER

132
00:08:58,420 --> 00:09:00,670
What's the matter? You don't want to?

133
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:03,710
If not, you can just go to prison instead.

134
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,840
No, sir.

135
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:27,150
Listen carefully.

136
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:31,410
You have to continue to be thick-skinned

137
00:09:31,990 --> 00:09:33,320
and pretend to be my fiancée.

138
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:38,330
Keep pretending to be your fiancée? Why?

139
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:40,000
You're a hostage. Are you questioning me?

140
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,420
No, I wasn't.

141
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:45,800
Behave well.

142
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:50,380
If you tell anyone
that I don't have amnesia,

143
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:54,010
it won't end with
just working for me without pay.

144
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,390
It'll be a vendetta

145
00:09:57,350 --> 00:09:58,850
beyond your imagination.

146
00:10:00,230 --> 00:10:02,520
A bloody revenge will follow.

147
00:10:10,450 --> 00:10:11,530
I'd be better…

148
00:10:12,910 --> 00:10:14,700
I'd be better off dying.

149
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:23,210
I want to go back!

150
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:27,050
The train is now approaching.

151
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:33,090
Mind the gap
between the train and the platform

152
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:35,930
as you get on and off the train.

153
00:10:57,950 --> 00:10:58,950
Have a good day.

154
00:11:06,330 --> 00:11:07,590
Thank you.

155
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,380
Here is your order.

156
00:11:11,970 --> 00:11:15,720
Pardon me.
You definitely removed the onions, right?

157
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,100
Yes.

158
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,810
Thank you.

159
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:24,560
Have a good day!

160
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:27,810
What was that?

161
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,860
I thought he had a new secretary.

162
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:35,490
I know. Ms. Gong said that Ms. Lee quit
to get ready for the wedding,

163
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:38,490
-and that a new secretary came.
-Yeah.

164
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:40,160
It's fake then.

165
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,410
Fake news.

166
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:46,620
Ms. Gong, the top informant
of Gotop Education,

167
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:48,460
could be so off like this.

168
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:53,250
Do you know what happens
when Earth's current temperature

169
00:13:53,630 --> 00:13:55,340
rises by one degree?

170
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:59,380
A giant glacier will melt down,

171
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:01,180
there will be endless famine,

172
00:14:01,260 --> 00:14:05,220
more than 50 million people
won't have sufficient water,

173
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:07,890
and 10% of land animals

174
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:10,100
will face the danger of extinction.

175
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:14,110
Thus, what does one degree
of temperature difference mean?

176
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:19,740
It's a tremendous
and unacceptable mistake.

177
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:29,410
The temperature of this coffee is
69 degrees Celsius.

178
00:14:30,330 --> 00:14:31,370
Unacceptable.

179
00:14:33,830 --> 00:14:35,250
What's with

180
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:37,340
that disrespectful expression?

181
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:41,970
You brought me lukewarm coffee
even a dog wouldn't want to drink.

182
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,300
I'll buy you a new one.

183
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:46,140
I'm sorry.

184
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:35,480
Perhaps the house is a bit dusty.

185
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:04,630
Gosh, my back.

186
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:16,140
I'll clean it quickly.
I'm cleaning it now.

187
00:16:37,460 --> 00:16:39,880
I'm suddenly craving bulgogi today.

188
00:16:41,670 --> 00:16:43,460
Is the place called, "Master's Bulgogi"?

189
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:47,090
I heard there's always
a line out the door there.

190
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:50,470
I see. I'll go get it right away.

191
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:12,490
I heard that eating too much meat
is terrible for your health.

192
00:17:13,330 --> 00:17:15,240
It would've been a disaster.

193
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:20,580
I want to eat very fresh…

194
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:24,170
very fresh live octopus.

195
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:30,890
Please prepare them well.

196
00:17:31,970 --> 00:17:33,180
Use lots of sesame oil.

197
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:36,310
Wait…

198
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:52,990
I can't eat it.

199
00:17:54,410 --> 00:17:56,290
I feel so bad for the octopus.

200
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:00,830
Oh well.

201
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,750
I'll just eat a sandwich.

202
00:18:02,830 --> 00:18:04,500
-What?
-What's wrong?

203
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,970
You said you'd do anything, right?

204
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,330
So handsome.

205
00:18:39,870 --> 00:18:42,580
NOH GOJIN
TOP INSTRUCTOR IN THE UNIVERSE

206
00:18:48,380 --> 00:18:49,510
Hello, sir.

207
00:18:55,390 --> 00:18:59,310
Something seems different, but not really.

208
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:02,600
They're beyond my comprehension.

209
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,650
Please follow me.

210
00:19:04,730 --> 00:19:06,060
Let's go inside.

211
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:10,280
-Hello.
-Hello.

212
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,570
-Hi, kids.
-Come this way.

213
00:19:15,740 --> 00:19:17,780
Do-re-mi-fa-sol

214
00:19:17,870 --> 00:19:19,330
I'll take care of it.

215
00:19:19,410 --> 00:19:21,540
-Can you summarize this?
-Sure, will do.

216
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,040
-Go now.
-How does this work?

217
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,750
Hey, go now.

218
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,040
-Gosh, there isn't much time.
-Hey, want drinks after?

219
00:19:27,130 --> 00:19:29,750
-Jeez, how can you drink every day?
-What's going on?

220
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:31,090
What's wrong?

221
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:38,390
What's going on?

222
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:40,390
-My goodness.
-What's going on?

223
00:19:40,970 --> 00:19:42,850
What are these cuties doing here?

224
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,140
What's going on?

225
00:19:47,190 --> 00:19:50,320
-So cute.
-They're already different, right?

226
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:53,280
The mothers in Gangnam already have
everything lined up for kids that age.

227
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:56,160
That's why they're visiting
the private education company already.

228
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,950
They're from Gotop's company daycare.

229
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,740
-I'll go with them.
-Sure.

230
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:02,080
What are
the company daycare kids doing here?

231
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:04,080
Let's follow them too.

232
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,290
Why would we do that?

233
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:07,670
Gosh, don't you get it?

234
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,340
It's for advertising.

235
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:11,000
They called the reporters to show off

236
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:13,880
that we're operating a company daycare.

237
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,340
Reporters?

238
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:20,010
That punk. He goes cheerfully
as long as there's a camera.

239
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:22,310
What?

240
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:24,180
Wait for me!

241
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:28,600
I'm going too.

242
00:20:34,990 --> 00:20:36,320
Come this way.

243
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,990
This way. Good job.

244
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,250
Over here?

245
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:00,890
What's going on here?

246
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:05,890
Did these people hear that I have amnesia?

247
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:22,580
-Sir, thank you for the on-time dismissal!
-Sir, thank you for the on-time dismissal!

248
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:24,620
On-time dismissal?

249
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:29,170
Sir, my kids are very happy with me.

250
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:33,170
It was hard for employees
with kids to work late,

251
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:36,130
but we get to go home
with our kids these days.

252
00:21:36,210 --> 00:21:38,220
Our kids love it so much.

253
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:40,720
Kids, do you remember what we prepared?

254
00:21:40,890 --> 00:21:43,100
Okay, begin!

255
00:21:43,180 --> 00:21:46,020
-Thank you!
-Thank you!

256
00:21:49,190 --> 00:21:50,770
-That's mine!
-Mine.

257
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:51,850
Mine!

258
00:21:51,940 --> 00:21:53,940
-Mine!
-Mine!

259
00:21:54,570 --> 00:21:55,480
No!

260
00:21:55,570 --> 00:21:59,280
Sir, thank you for letting us pull
our monthly paid vacation days together.

261
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:02,160
I got to go see my family
on my mother's birthday

262
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,570
without worrying about my in-laws.

263
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,160
Monthly paid vacation?

264
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:08,040
Sir, the beef was so delicious.

265
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:10,120
