to hear me suffer.

525
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:39,800
Thank you for your thoughts.

526
00:44:39,890 --> 00:44:41,100
Of course.

527
00:44:42,470 --> 00:44:44,680
I thought

528
00:44:45,810 --> 00:44:48,060
you weren't coming, Mr. Noh.
What a surprise.

529
00:44:49,060 --> 00:44:50,900
Why wouldn't I come?

530
00:44:52,070 --> 00:44:55,950
Were you hoping that I wouldn't come?

531
00:44:56,530 --> 00:44:58,030
Because of the incident with your wife.

532
00:44:59,950 --> 00:45:02,030
I trust that you received the bags?

533
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:06,660
What bags?

534
00:45:06,750 --> 00:45:10,210
At a department store recently--

535
00:45:10,290 --> 00:45:13,130
Mr. Noh. I heard that
you'll be publishing new study guides

536
00:45:13,710 --> 00:45:14,840
at the end of next month.

537
00:45:15,510 --> 00:45:16,920
You should stay alert.

538
00:45:17,010 --> 00:45:21,220
Mr. Park might replace
your study guide top sales record.

539
00:45:22,140 --> 00:45:23,720
The third set is already sold out, right?

540
00:45:23,810 --> 00:45:26,850
Gosh. The fourth set.

541
00:45:27,440 --> 00:45:29,400
-Already? The fourth set?
-The fourth set?

542
00:45:29,810 --> 00:45:33,110
Wow, you're amazing.

543
00:45:33,230 --> 00:45:34,070
You really are.

544
00:45:49,250 --> 00:45:52,290
GOTOP EDUCATION DEPUTY CEO OH SEGI

545
00:45:55,550 --> 00:45:58,090
You cherished Mr. Kang Min too, right?

546
00:45:58,170 --> 00:46:02,550
So I take your word for it
when it comes to most things, however…

547
00:46:02,640 --> 00:46:04,760
I take your word for it
when it comes to most things.

548
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,750
Great watch.

549
00:46:33,670 --> 00:46:34,790
What? Out of the blue?

550
00:46:37,300 --> 00:46:38,510
It looks nice.

551
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:46,640
It's bleeding.

552
00:46:52,770 --> 00:46:54,270
10-YEAR ANNIVERSARY
KPEDA REGULAR EVENT

553
00:47:01,990 --> 00:47:04,620
Sir! We have a problem.

554
00:47:06,030 --> 00:47:07,740
What is it? Why are you making a fuss?

555
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:22,720
There are comments posted
saying our guides have errors.

556
00:47:23,220 --> 00:47:25,550
What do you mean by errors?

557
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:29,180
NUMBER 10 ON PAGE 78 IS WEIRD
I WANT A REFUND

558
00:47:29,270 --> 00:47:30,180
What's all this?

559
00:47:30,270 --> 00:47:31,890
DID YOU REVIEW IT PROPERLY?
WASTE OF MONEY

560
00:47:33,940 --> 00:47:34,770
Thief.

561
00:47:36,770 --> 00:47:37,730
What did you say?

562
00:47:39,070 --> 00:47:40,110
What did you just say?

563
00:47:40,190 --> 00:47:43,360
You stole my study guides.

564
00:47:43,450 --> 00:47:45,950
Have you lost your mind?
When did I do that?

565
00:47:46,740 --> 00:47:48,780
Do you have evidence? Do you?

566
00:47:49,490 --> 00:47:50,620
Evidence?

567
00:47:51,910 --> 00:47:53,750
I planted…

568
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:56,920
fifteen erroneous questions inside.

569
00:47:57,960 --> 00:47:58,790
What?

570
00:47:58,880 --> 00:48:00,460
A special event.

571
00:48:01,380 --> 00:48:03,800
I was going to give gifts
to the first 100 students

572
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,340
who find the erroneous questions.

573
00:48:05,930 --> 00:48:06,930
The latest cell phone.

574
00:48:07,680 --> 00:48:11,220
Perhaps because the questions are hard,
it's taking a little while.

575
00:48:12,770 --> 00:48:14,390
But you'll be flooded with complaints now.

576
00:48:15,190 --> 00:48:17,020
What are you talking about?

577
00:48:18,480 --> 00:48:19,980
You didn't even review them, did you?

578
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:25,530
I told my research team
that I reviewed them all myself,

579
00:48:25,610 --> 00:48:29,580
and that they were the final version
to be published right away.

580
00:48:31,240 --> 00:48:32,750
You should've tried solving them.

581
00:48:33,870 --> 00:48:37,580
But I doubt you could've found the errors
since your brain is rusty.

582
00:48:40,130 --> 00:48:43,130
That's how you become
old and insignificant, Mr. Park.

583
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:50,470
You opened the Champagne bottle too early.

584
00:48:54,180 --> 00:48:56,390
You're no match for me. Do you know why?

585
00:48:57,600 --> 00:48:59,610
Because I was destroyed by you before.

586
00:49:14,950 --> 00:49:16,210
It's not true.

587
00:49:16,750 --> 00:49:20,080
That punk is bluffing me.

588
00:49:20,630 --> 00:49:23,210
He's blinded by jealousy,
so he's lying to me.

589
00:49:23,300 --> 00:49:25,010
He's lying…

590
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:28,720
-Oh no!
-Mr. Park!

591
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:30,260
-Wake up, Mr. Park!
-Gosh.

592
00:49:30,340 --> 00:49:32,600
-Mr. Park!
-Wake up, Mr. Park!

593
00:49:32,680 --> 00:49:34,520
-Mr. Park!
-Call an ambulance!

594
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:39,560
10-YEAR ANNIVERSARY
KPEDA REGULAR EVENT

595
00:49:41,310 --> 00:49:42,440
Did we come too late?

596
00:49:42,770 --> 00:49:44,650
The star of the show always comes last.

597
00:49:45,780 --> 00:49:48,900
Then I have time
to check myself in the mirror, right?

598
00:49:49,110 --> 00:49:50,110
Yes.

599
00:50:11,390 --> 00:50:12,390
Great.

600
00:50:13,890 --> 00:50:14,970
Perfect.

601
00:50:20,770 --> 00:50:21,770
It hurts.

602
00:50:24,770 --> 00:50:27,110
Oh, my. Thank you…

603
00:50:27,570 --> 00:50:29,400
Oh, Ms. Sooyeong!

604
00:50:30,110 --> 00:50:31,200
Ms. Sina!

605
00:50:32,820 --> 00:50:36,540
Wow, you look so pretty.
I almost didn't recognize you.

606
00:50:38,120 --> 00:50:41,500
No, you look
so much more beautiful than me.

607
00:50:42,500 --> 00:50:44,040
We run into each other often.

608
00:50:44,790 --> 00:50:45,630
Tell me about it.

609
00:50:47,670 --> 00:50:50,720
I guess you don't wear heels very often.

610
00:50:52,010 --> 00:50:54,430
No, since I always
have to run around for work,

611
00:50:54,510 --> 00:50:56,220
I generally don't prefer to wear heels.

612
00:50:56,310 --> 00:50:59,390
But higher things are great,
so don't give them up.

613
00:51:00,140 --> 00:51:03,190
Maybe because I'm a country bumpkin.
Heels aren't for me.

614
00:51:03,270 --> 00:51:06,610
Don't worry. If you wear them often,
you'll get used to them.

615
00:51:08,230 --> 00:51:13,660
By the way, you said last time
you work at Gotop Education, right?

616
00:51:13,740 --> 00:51:17,160
Yes, I came here today
because our CEO is attending the event.

617
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:21,120
By any chance, are you Gojin--

618
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:25,420
Are you Gotop Education CEO's secretary?

619
00:51:25,540 --> 00:51:26,380
Yes.

620
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:31,760
Wow, what a small world.

621
00:51:33,510 --> 00:51:35,430
We're sharing a man.

622
00:51:36,180 --> 00:51:37,010
Pardon?

623
00:51:38,260 --> 00:51:39,100
Nothing.

624
00:51:40,560 --> 00:51:42,350
What brings you here today?

625
00:51:42,430 --> 00:51:45,480
You'll find out soon.
See you in a little bit then.

626
00:51:45,900 --> 00:51:46,900
Okay.

627
00:51:58,580 --> 00:51:59,620
My goodness. What happened?

628
00:52:03,370 --> 00:52:05,500
They think
Park Yangtae had sleeping pills.

629
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:09,040
I heard the study guides are
full of errors. I guess he feels ashamed.

630
00:52:18,390 --> 00:52:21,350
But what's taking this woman so long?

631
00:52:34,150 --> 00:52:34,990
Look, sir.

632
00:52:35,530 --> 00:52:38,740
My goodness. You're here.

633
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:42,120
-Hello, sir.
-Hello.

634
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,000
Where is Mr. Park Yangtae?

635
00:52:44,870 --> 00:52:48,500
He had an urgent personal matter.

636
00:52:48,580 --> 00:52:50,960
In any case, welcome.

637
00:52:51,630 --> 00:52:53,090
I'm not even qualified yet.

638
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:56,050
I hope I'm not inconveniencing you
by attending today.

639
00:52:56,130 --> 00:52:58,510
Please don't say that.

640
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:01,180
It's an honor to have you at the KPEDA.

641
00:53:01,260 --> 00:53:03,060
I'm glad you came.

642
00:53:03,770 --> 00:53:05,230
One moment, please.

643
00:53:05,310 --> 00:53:09,020
Okay, everyone.
May I have your attention, please?

644
00:53:09,770 --> 00:53:13,860
She recently acquired Eutteum School
and launched Baek Edu.

645
00:53:13,940 --> 00:53:15,900
She's the youngest daughter
of Gunil Group's owner

646
00:53:16,530 --> 00:53:18,490
as well as the newest member of KPEDA.

647
00:53:19,200 --> 00:53:22,910
Let me introduce
CEO Baek Sooyeong of Baek Edu.

648
00:53:31,090 --> 00:53:34,840
Oh, right. And Eutteum School was
acquired by Gunil Group.

649
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:36,920
Hello.

650
00:53:37,510 --> 00:53:40,010
Say hello. He's the Minister
of the Department of Education.

651
00:53:40,260 --> 00:53:41,680
-Hello. Nice to meet you.
-Hello.

652
00:54:00,110 --> 00:54:01,490
Mr. Noh Gojin.

653
00:54:02,700 --> 00:54:05,580
My name is Baek Sooyeong
I'm the CEO of Baek Edu.

654
00:54:21,590 --> 00:54:22,590
Higher things?

655
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:26,890
The best is having peace of mind.

656
00:54:35,230 --> 00:54:37,990
CEO of Baek Edu?

657
00:54:40,610 --> 00:54:43,530
I'm sorry for not telling you sooner.

658
00:54:44,830 --> 00:54:50,040
I wanted us to be friends
who feel comfortable around each other.

659
00:54:52,580 --> 00:54:56,960
Why on earth
are you back in my life again?

660
00:54:59,590 --> 00:55:00,720
Are you upset?

661
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:05,430
So are you not going to be my friend?

662
00:55:12,980 --> 00:55:15,190
Fine. Let's be friends.

663
00:55:17,110 --> 00:55:20,530
I have someone
I want to introduce to my friend.

664
00:55:34,330 --> 00:55:35,670
Please say hello.

665
00:55:36,630 --> 00:55:39,340
This is my fiancée Lee Sina.

666
00:55:42,420 --> 00:55:45,430
Fian… Fiancée?

667
00:55:47,390 --> 00:55:48,310
Say hello, honey.

668
00:55:50,100 --> 00:55:51,390
She's the CEO of Baek Edu.

669
00:55:59,530 --> 00:56:02,440
We have many things to celebrate today.

670
00:56:03,400 --> 00:56:06,990
Gotop Education CEO Noh Gojin
has gotten engaged.

671
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:09,160
Let's all congratulate him.

672
00:56:11,370 --> 00:56:13,830
-Congratulations!
-Congratulations!

673
00:56:30,850 --> 00:56:33,270
My fiancée feels uncomfortable
at events like this,

674
00:56:34,520 --> 00:56:36,400
so we just came to say hello today.

675
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:39,480
Well, then.

676
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:44,860
We'll be going off to have a date now.

677
00:56:50,120 --> 00:56:51,120
Please excuse us.

678
00:56:56,330 --> 00:56:57,330
Congratulations, sir.

679
00:56:57,830 --> 00:57:00,290
-Congratulations!
-All right!

680
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:19,480
10-YEAR ANNIVERSARY
KPEDA REGULAR EVENT

681
00:57:29,950 --> 00:57:30,780
Noh Gojin!

682
00:57:38,120 --> 00:57:39,080
Three seconds.

683
00:57:41,670 --> 00:57:43,250
I need your permission.

684
00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:46,130
-Pardon?
-But I'm not going to ask for it.

685
00:57:51,720 --> 00:57:52,720
Because I'm…

686
00:57:54,930 --> 00:57:56,310
so desperate right now.

687
00:57:57,060 --> 00:57:58,190
What do you mean…

688
01:01:03,700 --> 01:01:05,710
Translated by Ji-young Hwang
